<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 03 at 5:08PM EDT  by NWS Grand Rapids</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southern Calhoun and
southeastern Kalamazoo Counties through 600 PM EDT...
At 506 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Burlington, or 12 miles southwest of Marshall, moving southwest at 10
mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Union City...      Burlington...      Fulton...
Athens...          Tekonsha...        Pine Creek...
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
